=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ E.\">E.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Or.\">Or.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">323</biblScope> </bibl>); the spellings <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀποτεινύτω</foreign> (Crete, <date TEIform=\"date\">v B.C.</date>), <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀποτειννυέτω</foreign> (Avrom., <date TEIform=\"date\">i B.C.</date>) (v. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀποτίνυμι</foreign>), and the form of the root (<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τῐ-</foreign>: <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τει-</foreign>: <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ποι-</foreign> (v. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τίνω</foreign>), never <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τῑ-</foreign>, which belongs only to <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τίω</foreign>) show that the true spellings are <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τεινυ-</foreign>, later <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τειννυ-</foreign>, still later <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τῑννυ-</foreign> with <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ι</itype> long by nature: the early forms <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀποτινυ[μεν</foreign> (v. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἀποτίνυμι</foreign>)<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">, [τ]ινυμε[νο]</foreign> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ GDI\">GDI</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">5125</biblScope> </bibl> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">A</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3</biblScope> </bibl> (<placeName TEIform=\"placeName\">Crete</placeName>) remain unexplained: <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τίν[υ]σθαι</foreign> is uncertain in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">12(9).1273</biblScope> </bibl> (p. viii) (Eretria, <date TEIform=\"date\">vi B.C.</date>): perh. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τῐνυ-</foreign> existed as well as <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">τεινυ-</foreign>.]</sense> </entryFree>"}]}